July will go away with heat, August will start with coolness
Over the weekend, Moscow and the region experienced the coldest night of July.
Of course, no frost chilling apocalypse occurred.
But for the top of the summer, it's a shame.
Before talking about the weather in Moscow on July 27 - August 2, 2020, it is worth noting that on the night of Saturday, July 25, the air cooled to + 8.8 degrees in the capital.
Kolomna even set a new temperature record: + 7 degrees (the previous minimum for July 25 has been held since 1964, more than half a century).
Cherusti became the cold pole near Moscow, where thermometers showed + 3.9 degrees.
However, in the afternoon, both Saturday and Sunday were quite comfortable.
Although, compared to climate norms, it is still 2 to 3 degrees cooler.
On working days, not just heat, but real heat will return to Moscow.
On Monday, July 27, the Russian Hydrometeorological Center promises + 26 degrees, on Tuesday and Wednesday + 28... + 29, on Thursday, July 30, + 26 degrees.
Short rains - every day in the middle of the week with thunderstorms.
The last day of July and the first days of August (that is, next weekend) will be cool, not higher than + 19... + 24 degrees.
And it will not do without rainfall.
A Rwandan confessed to setting fire to a cathedral in Nantes
A native of Rwanda, who worked at the Cathedral of Saints Peter and Paul in the French city of Nantes on a voluntary basis, admitted arson a week after the fire.
This was reported on Sunday by the France-3 television channel.
According to him, the man, who had already been detained on July 19, the day after the fire, was detained again the day before.
On Saturday evening, he appeared before an investigating judge.
After being charged with intentional damage to property, the man admitted that he had set fire to three places - under a large organ, under a small organ and at an electric shield.
Now he faces up to 10 years in prison and a fine of 150 thousand euros.
The motives of the 39-year-old from Rwanda have not yet been reported.
It is only known that he voluntarily helped in the cathedral and on the day of the fire had to close its doors.
However, according to CCTV footage, he left the religious institution 15 minutes after receiving calls about a fire in the building.
The fire in the Cathedral of Saints Peter and Paul occurred on July 18.
More than 200 firefighters fought for several hours for the Gothic architectural monument.
However, they failed to save Louis XII stained glass windows and a unique Baroque organ.
The situation was brought under control only three hours after the start of the fire.
No one was injured in the incident.
The current fire is not the first during the existence of the temple.
In 1972, fire destroyed its roof.
It took 13 years to eliminate the consequences of that fire.
For parishioners, the cathedral was reopened only in 1985.
